*
***    DEFINE GLOBAL REVIEW OS LEVEL SWITCHES
         GBLB  &ENV390
         GBLB  &ENVESA
         GBLB  &ENVBIG
         GBLB  &ENVZV2
*
***    SET ALL OF THESE FLAGS TO 0 FOR FREELY AVAILABLE
***    VERSIONS OF MVS SUCH AS MVS 3.8J.
*
***    &ENV390 SHOULD ONLY BE SET TO 1 WITH AN ASSEMBLE-TIME
***    ENVIRONMENT OF OS/390 VERSION 2 OR LATER.
***
&ENV390  SETB  1                   1 - OS/390 V2 AND LATER
***                                0 - PRE-OS/390 V2 MACLIBS
*
*
***    &ENVESA SHOULD ONLY BE SET TO 1 WHEN THE RUN-TIME
***    ENVIRONMENT WILL DEFINITELY SUPPORT DATA SPACE USAGE.
***
&ENVESA  SETB  1                   1 - USE DATA SPACE UP TO 2GB
***                                0 - USE REGION
***
***    SETTING &ENVESA TO 0 WILL CAUSE REVEDIT TO HOLD DATA
***    BEING EDITED IN THE USER REGION AND NOT A DATA SPACE.
***
***    SETTING &ENVESA TO 0 SHOULD PRODUCE A LOAD MODULE WHICH WILL
***    RUN ON ANY RELEASE OF MVS EVER (NOT TESTED ON 3.7 OR EARLIER).
*
&ENVBIG  SETB  1                   1 - DSNTYPE=LARGE IS SUPPORTED
***                                0 - DSNTYPE=LARGE NOT SUPPORTED
*
***    &ENVZV2 SHOULD ONLY BE SET TO 1 WITH AN ASSEMBLE-TIME
***    ENVIRONMENT OF Z/OS VERSION 2 OR LATER.  REQUIRES &ENV390.
***
&ENVZV2  SETB  1                   1 - Z/OS V2 AND LATER
***                                0 - PRE-Z/OS V2 MACLIBS
*
